	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Louis</placeName>&#44; <date>May 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1857</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44; <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear friend&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I <sic>dont</sic> know <sic>wether</sic> you can<lb/> use the enclosed article and I am not hurt<lb/> in the least if you tell me it is not worth<lb/> <del>a dam</del>.  I feel that I have not looked<lb/> around with a sufficiently searching mind<lb/> to make a complete and correct report.<lb/>  But I believe that I have told the<lb/> truth.  Should you decide to print it&#44; then<lb/> I wish you would correct my bad English.<lb/>  Although I generally do not do it&#44; but this<lb/> case you may be at liberty to add or leave off<lb/> as you see fit&#44; for I can readily see the<lb/> lack of better <del> <add>&#63;</add> </del> comprehension.  I should have<lb/> added that for the first time I preached here<lb/> in the German language on <date>Rosh Hashannah</date>.<lb/>  The congregation might have gotten some<lb/> new members.  The Bavarian congregation<lb/> followed this example at once.  But I <sic>dont</sic><lb/> want to talk about myself nor do I wish<lb/> to go into details.  In the near future I hope<lb/> to send you an entirely different contribution</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p rend="align(center)">&#45;2&#45;</p>
				<p>which might have more value.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I am happy&#44; honest to God happy<lb/> that you continued the Occident and I<lb/> am only sorry that I cannot do anything<lb/> to further its distribution.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">When you come to <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> I want you to see my Seferim.  Especially<lb/> &#124; &#124; &#124; ask for my <add>Hebrew</add> <add>&#63;</add> <add>Pahad Yitzhak</add>&#44; the great and rare<lb/> talmudic REAL &#40;ANAL&#63;&#41; LEXICON &#40;dictionary&#41;.<lb/>  Only a few copies are in existence and none are<lb/> sold in book stores.  <persName>Dr. Zunz</persName>&#44; <persName>Sachs</persName> and<lb/> <persName>Rappoport</persName> paid 30&#162; for a copy.  <del>It will be<lb/>of gre</del> It will greatly assist you in your<lb/> work and you get 30&#37; off the list price.<lb/>  You need not spend a cent and I can in this<lb/> manner not only pay off my debt&#44; but also the &#36;3.&#8212; for the new subscriptions of the Occident.<lb/>  And moreover I would consider it a favor&#44;<lb/> for which I promise to be thankful in later<lb/> years when I God helping&#44; will find myself<lb/> in better financial strength.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your very truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Isidor Bush</persName></p>
				<p>He probably meant &#36;</p>
		</body>
